README.md
     1‚Üílog
     4‚ÜíA Rust library providing a lightweight logging *facade*.
     5‚Üí
     6‚Üí[![Build status](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/rust-lang/log/main.yml?branch=master)](https://github.com/rust-lang/log/actions)
     7‚Üí[![Latest version](https://img.shields.io/crates/v/log.svg)](https://crates.io/crates/log)
     8‚Üí[![Documentation](https://docs.rs/log/badge.svg)](https://docs.rs/log)
     9‚Üí![License](https://img.shields.io/crates/l/log.svg)
    10‚Üí
    11‚Üí* [`log` documentation](https://docs.rs/log)
    12‚Üí
    13‚ÜíA logging facade provides a single logging API that abstracts over the actual
    14‚Üílogging implementation. Libraries can use the logging API provided by this
    15‚Üícrate, and the consumer of those libraries can choose the logging
    16‚Üíimplementation that is most suitable for its use case.
    17‚Üí
    18‚Üí
    19‚Üí## Minimum supported `rustc`
    21‚Üí`1.68.0+`
    22‚Üí
    23‚ÜíThis version is explicitly tested in CI and may be bumped in any release as needed. Maintaining compatibility with older compilers is a priority though, so the bar for bumping the minimum supported version is set very high. Any changes to the supported minimum version will be called out in the release notes.
    24‚Üí
    25‚Üí## Usage
    27‚Üí### In libraries
    29‚ÜíLibraries should link only to the `log` crate, and use the provided macros to
    30‚Üílog whatever information will be useful to downstream consumers:
    31‚Üí
    32‚Üí```toml
    33‚Üí[dependencies]
    34‚Üílog = "0.4"
    35‚Üí```
    36‚Üí
    37‚Üí```rust
    38‚Üíuse log::{info, trace, warn};
    39‚Üí
    40‚Üípub fn shave_the_yak(yak: &mut Yak) {
    41‚Üí    trace!("Commencing yak shaving");
    42‚Üí
    43‚Üí    loop {
    44‚Üí        match find_a_razor() {
    45‚Üí            Ok(razor) => {
    46‚Üí                info!("Razor located: {razor}");
    47‚Üí                yak.shave(razor);
    48‚Üí                break;
    49‚Üí            }
    50‚Üí            Err(err) => {
    51‚Üí                warn!("Unable to locate a razor: {err}, retrying");
    52‚Üí            }
    53‚Üí        }
    54‚Üí    }
    55‚Üí}
    56‚Üí```
    57‚Üí
    58‚Üí### In executables
    60‚ÜíIn order to produce log output, executables have to use a logger implementation compatible with the facade.
    61‚ÜíThere are many available implementations to choose from, here are some options:
    62‚Üí
    63‚Üí* Simple minimal loggers:
    64‚Üí    * [`env_logger`](https://docs.rs/env_logger/*/env_logger/)
    65‚Üí    * [`colog`](https://docs.rs/colog/*/colog/)
    66‚Üí    * [`simple_logger`](https://docs.rs/simple_logger/*/simple_logger/)
    67‚Üí    * [`simplelog`](https://docs.rs/simplelog/*/simplelog/)
    68‚Üí    * [`pretty_env_logger`](https://docs.rs/pretty_env_logger/*/pretty_env_logger/)
    69‚Üí    * [`stderrlog`](https://docs.rs/stderrlog/*/stderrlog/)
    70‚Üí    * [`flexi_logger`](https://docs.rs/flexi_logger/*/flexi_logger/)
    71‚Üí    * [`call_logger`](https://docs.rs/call_logger/*/call_logger/)
    72‚Üí    * [`std-logger`](https://docs.rs/std-logger/*/std_logger/)
    73‚Üí    * [`structured-logger`](https://docs.rs/structured-logger/latest/structured_logger/)
    74‚Üí    * [`clang_log`](https://docs.rs/clang_log/latest/clang_log)
    75‚Üí    * [`ftail`](https://docs.rs/ftail/latest/ftail/)
    76‚Üí* Complex configurable frameworks:
    77‚Üí    * [`log4rs`](https://docs.rs/log4rs/*/log4rs/)
    78‚Üí    * [`logforth`](https://docs.rs/logforth/*/logforth/)
    79‚Üí    * [`fern`](https://docs.rs/fern/*/fern/)
    80‚Üí    * [`spdlog-rs`](https://docs.rs/spdlog-rs/*/spdlog/)
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   106‚Üí## Structured logging
   108‚ÜíIf you enable the `kv` feature, you can associate structured data with your log records:
   109‚Üí
   110‚Üí```rust
   111‚Üíuse log::{info, trace, warn};
   112‚Üí
   113‚Üípub fn shave_the_yak(yak: &mut Yak) {
   114‚Üí    // `yak:serde` will capture `yak` using its `serde::Serialize` impl
   115‚Üí    //
   116‚Üí    // You could also use `:?` for `Debug`, or `:%` for `Display`. For a
   117‚Üí    // full list, see the `log` crate documentation
   118‚Üí    trace!(target = "yak_events", yak:serde; "Commencing yak shaving");
   119‚Üí
   120‚Üí    loop {
   121‚Üí        match find_a_razor() {
   122‚Üí            Ok(razor) => {
   123‚Üí                info!(razor; "Razor located");
   124‚Üí                yak.shave(razor);
   125‚Üí                break;
   126‚Üí            }
   127‚Üí            Err(e) => {
   128‚Üí                // `e:err` will capture `e` using its `std::error::Error` impl
   129‚Üí                warn!(e:err; "Unable to locate a razor, retrying");
   130‚Üí            }
   131‚Üí        }
   132‚Üí    }
   133‚Üí}
   134‚Üí```
rfcs/0296-structured-logging.md
     5‚Üí# Summary
     8‚ÜíAdd support for structured logging to the `log` crate in both `std` and `no_std` environments, allowing log records to carry typed data beyond a textual message. This document serves as an introduction to what structured logging is all about, and as an RFC for an implementation in the `log` crate.
     9‚Üí
    10‚Üí`log` will provide an API for capturing structured data that offloads complex serialization to de-facto standards in the ecosystem, but avoids integrating them too tightly, or forcing any specific framework on consumers.
    11‚Üí
    12‚ÜíThe API is heavily inspired by `slog` and `tokio-trace`.
    13‚Üí
    14‚Üí> NOTE: Code in this RFC uses recent language features like `impl Trait`, but can be implemented without them.
    15‚Üí
    16‚Üí# Contents
    17‚Üí- [Motivation](#motivation)
    18‚Üí  - [What is structured logging?](#what-is-structured-logging)
    19‚Üí  - [Why do we need structured logging in `log`?](#why-do-we-need-structured-logging-in-log)
    20‚Üí- [Guide-level explanation](#guide-level-explanation)
    21‚Üí  - [Logging structured key-value pairs](#logging-structured-key-value-pairs)
    22‚Üí  - [Supporting key-value pairs in `Log` implementations](#supporting-key-value-pairs-in-log-implementations)
    23‚Üí  - [Integrating log frameworks with `log`](#integrating-log-frameworks-with-log)
    24‚Üí  - [How producers and consumers of structured values interact](#how-producers-and-consumers-of-structured-values-interact)
    25‚Üí- [Reference-level explanation](#reference-level-explanation)
    26‚Üí  - [Design considerations](#design-considerations)
    27‚Üí  - [Cargo features](#cargo-features)
    28‚Üí  - [A complete key-values API](#a-complete-key-values-api)
    29‚Üí    - [`Error`](#error)
